# Sales Management Plugin\\par
## Client User Guide + Complete Test Plan\\par
\\par
Document Version: 1.0  \\par
Prepared On: February 28, 2026  \\par
Audience: Store Owners, Cashiers/Salesmen, Administrators, QA/Client Review Team\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
## 1. Purpose of This Document\\par
This document is designed for two goals:\\par
1. Help your client use the plugin correctly in daily operations.\\par
2. Provide a full step-by-step testing guide to verify each feature before go-live.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
## 2. Plugin Features Covered\\par
This guide covers all major plugin pages and flows:\\par
1. Sales Entry\\par
2. Sales Listing and Today Summary\\par
3. Products and Manufacturers\\par
4. Purchases\\par
5. Pending Payments (Sale Recoveries + Purchase Payments)\\par
6. Customers\\par
7. Returns\\par
8. Stock\\par
9. Invoice Details (Sale and Purchase)\\par
10. Analytics\\par
11. Salesman Authentication (User + Pincode)\\par
12. Receipt/Print output validation\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
## 3. Roles and Access\\par
Recommended operational roles:\\par
1. Administrator\\par
- Configure plugin and users.\\par
- Set sales pincode for each salesman.\\par
- Manage all pages.\\par
\\par
2. Salesman/Cashier\\par
- Create sales entries.\\par
- Authenticate in popup with selected user + pincode.\\par
- Print and save bills.\\par
\\par
3. Accountant/Manager\\par
- Review sales, purchases, pending payments, customers, and analytics.\\par
\\par
Important:\\par
- Sales authentication uses a dedicated pincode field in WordPress User Profile.\\par
- It is separate from WordPress login password.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
## 4. Pre-Setup Checklist (Before Testing or Go-Live)\\par
Complete this once:\\par
1. Activate plugin in WordPress.\\par
2. Confirm plugin menu is visible in admin.\\par
3. Go to `Users > Edit User` for each salesperson.\\par
4. Set `Sales Pincode` (4 to 10 digits), then save.\\par
5. Add at least 3 manufacturers.\\par
6. Add at least 5 products (different vendors/manufacturers).\\par
7. Add opening stock via Purchase page (paid and unpaid examples).\\par
8. Confirm Pending Payments page shows dues for unpaid/partial purchases.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
## 5. Daily Operational Flow (Recommended)\\par
Use this exact order daily:\\par
1. Record Purchases to update stock.\\par
2. Perform Sales (Cash, Credit, Partially Paid) through Sales Entry.\\par
3. Receive/pay due amounts from Pending Payments.\\par
4. Process Returns if needed.\\par
5. Review Sales page Today Summary and Cash In Hand.\\par
6. Verify physical cash against `Total Cash In Hand`.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
## 6. Feature Usage Guide\\par
\\par
### 6.1 Products Page\\par
Use for product and manufacturer master data.\\par
\\par
Steps:\\par
1. Open `Products` page.\\par
2. Add manufacturer from Manufacturers panel.\\par
3. Add product with:\\par
- Name\\par
- Purchase Price\\par
- Sale Price\\par
- Min Quantity\\par
- Vendor\\par
- Manufacturer\\par
- Location\\par
4. Use quick edit to update product details.\\par
\\par
Expected behavior:\\par
1. Product appears in listing.\\par
2. Manufacturer mapping is visible.\\par
3. Stock starts from 0 until purchased.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.2 Purchase Page\\par
Use for stock entry and vendor payment tracking.\\par
\\par
Steps:\\par
1. Open `Purchase` page.\\par
2. Click `Add New Purchase`.\\par
3. Add one or more products.\\par
4. Set payment status:\\par
- Paid\\par
- Unpaid\\par
- Partially Paid\\par
5. Enter vendor and optional description.\\par
6. Save purchase.\\par
\\par
Expected behavior:\\par
1. Purchase row appears with `Payment`, `Paid`, and `Remaining` columns.\\par
2. Stock increases.\\par
3. For unpaid/partial purchases, due is created in Pending Payments.\\par
4. Purchase invoice details are printable and linked from Pending Payments.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.3 Sales Entry Page\\par
Use to generate and save sales with receipt printing.\\par
\\par
Steps:\\par
1. Open `Sales Management` main page.\\par
2. Add products to selected list.\\par
3. Enter quantity and optional discount.\\par
4. Select Sales Type:\\par
- Cash Sale\\par
- Credit Sale\\par
- Partially Paid\\par
5. For Credit/Partial:\\par
- Fill customer name and phone in popup.\\par
6. Click `Print and Save`.\\par
7. In auth popup:\\par
- Select salesman from dropdown.\\par
- Enter pincode.\\par
- Confirm.\\par
\\par
Expected behavior:\\par
1. Customer form validates required fields before auth popup.\\par
2. Customer popup closes before auth popup opens.\\par
3. Wrong pincode shows inline error (not browser alert).\\par
4. Sale is saved only after successful auth.\\par
5. Receipt includes correct financial and account status details.\\par
6. Credit/partial sale creates due entry and appears in Pending Payments.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.4 Sales Listing + Today Summary\\par
Open `Sales` page.\\par
\\par
Today Summary includes:\\par
1. Today's Sale\\par
2. Today's Purchase\\par
3. Today's Profit\\par
4. Today's Discount\\par
5. Today's Recovery\\par
6. Today's Payments (Paid)\\par
7. Total Cash In Hand\\par
\\par
Formula:\\par
`Cash In Hand = (Cash Sale + Initial Received + Recovery) - (Initial Purchase Paid + Payments Paid)`\\par
\\par
Use this value to match physical cash.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.5 Pending Payments Page\\par
Central page for dues.\\par
\\par
Capabilities:\\par
1. Filter by status: Open / Closed / All\\par
2. Filter by due type: Sale / Purchase\\par
3. Separate `Customer` and `Vendor` columns\\par
4. Invoice column links directly to affected Sale/Purchase invoice details\\par
5. Action button changes by due type:\\par
- Sale due: `Receive Payment`\\par
- Purchase due: `Pay Payment`\\par
\\par
Expected behavior:\\par
1. Payment history updates.\\par
2. Remaining amount decreases.\\par
3. Status closes at zero remaining.\\par
4. Related sale/purchase master record is updated.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.6 Customers Page\\par
Open `Customers` page.\\par
\\par
Shows:\\par
1. Customer profile fields\\par
2. Total sales count\\par
3. Total sales amount\\par
4. Open due amount\\par
5. Last invoice (linked)\\par
\\par
Important logic:\\par
- Credit/partial sale customer matching is based on phone number.\\par
- Existing customer is reused if phone already exists.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.7 Returns Page\\par
Use for product return against invoice.\\par
\\par
Steps:\\par
1. Enter invoice number.\\par
2. Select invoiced product.\\par
3. Enter return quantity/reason.\\par
4. Submit return.\\par
\\par
Expected behavior:\\par
1. Return appears in returns listing.\\par
2. Stock is adjusted back.\\par
3. Return amount and date are recorded.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.8 Stock Page\\par
Shows current stock valuation.\\par
\\par
Outputs include:\\par
1. Quantity\\par
2. Purchase/Sale rates\\par
3. Purchase amount\\par
4. Sale amount\\par
5. Profit per product\\par
6. Totals in footer\\par
\\par
Expected behavior:\\par
- Low stock and zero stock rows are visibly highlighted.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.9 Invoice Detail Pages (Sale and Purchase)\\par
Use linked invoice pages for audit and print.\\par
\\par
Expected sale invoice fields:\\par
1. Customer Name\\par
2. Invoice No\\par
3. Item table\\par
4. Total items, gross, discount, net\\par
5. Sales person\\par
6. Paid amount\\par
7. Payment history\\par
8. Remaining amount\\par
9. Account status\\par
10. Payment status\\par
11. Sale type\\par
12. Payment method (when applicable)\\par
\\par
Expected purchase invoice fields:\\par
1. Salesman\\par
2. Invoice No\\par
3. Invoice type\\par
4. Vendor\\par
5. Item table\\par
6. Total payment\\par
7. Paid amount\\par
8. Payment history\\par
9. Remaining amount\\par
10. Account status\\par
11. Payment status\\par
12. Payment method (when applicable)\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 6.10 Analytics Page\\par
Use for management reporting:\\par
1. Top selling products\\par
2. Most profitable products\\par
3. Low stock alerts\\par
4. Recent sales\\par
5. Monthly sales chart\\par
6. Product performance chart\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
## 7. Full End-to-End Testing Guide\\par
Run this in a fresh test cycle and capture screenshots.\\par
\\par
### 7.1 Access and Security Tests\\par
\\par
Test A01: Admin access\\par
1. Login as admin.\\par
2. Open each plugin submenu page.\\par
Expected: All pages load without permission errors.\\par
\\par
Test A02: Sales pincode field\\par
1. Open `Users > Edit User`.\\par
2. Set pincode and save.\\par
3. Reload page.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Pincode input stays blank (security).\\par
2. Status shows `Set`.\\par
3. Last updated timestamp is visible.\\par
\\par
Test A03: Clear pincode\\par
1. Tick `Clear current pincode` and save.\\par
Expected: Status becomes `Not set`.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 7.2 Products and Manufacturer Tests\\par
\\par
Test P01: Add manufacturer\\par
1. Add new manufacturer.\\par
Expected: New manufacturer appears in list.\\par
\\par
Test P02: Duplicate manufacturer\\par
1. Add same name again.\\par
Expected: Duplicate prevention message appears.\\par
\\par
Test P03: Add product\\par
1. Add product with valid values.\\par
Expected: Product appears in products table.\\par
\\par
Test P04: Edit product\\par
1. Quick edit product name/rates/location.\\par
Expected: Updated values save and display.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 7.3 Purchase Tests\\par
\\par
Test PU01: Paid purchase\\par
1. Create purchase with `Paid` status.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Purchase listing shows paid amount = total, remaining = 0.\\par
2. No open due in Pending Payments.\\par
\\par
Test PU02: Unpaid purchase\\par
1. Create purchase with `Unpaid` status.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Due appears in Pending Payments as Purchase type.\\par
2. Vendor column is populated.\\par
3. Invoice link opens purchase invoice details page.\\par
\\par
Test PU03: Partial purchase\\par
1. Create purchase with partial paid amount.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Remaining > 0 in purchase listing.\\par
2. Due is open in Pending Payments.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 7.4 Sales Entry Tests\\par
\\par
Test S01: Cash sale\\par
1. Add products and quantities.\\par
2. Sales Type = Cash Sale.\\par
3. Print and Save with auth success.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Sale saved.\\par
2. No pending due created.\\par
3. Receipt shows paid as full and remaining 0.\\par
\\par
Test S02: Credit sale validation\\par
1. Sales Type = Credit Sale.\\par
2. Click Print and Save without customer name/phone.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Inline validation errors on required customer fields.\\par
2. Auth popup does not open.\\par
\\par
Test S03: Credit sale save flow\\par
1. Fill customer name + phone.\\par
2. Print and Save.\\par
3. In auth popup select user + correct pincode.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Customer popup closes before auth popup.\\par
2. Sale saves successfully.\\par
3. Due entry appears in Pending Payments.\\par
\\par
Test S04: Partially paid sale\\par
1. Sales Type = Partially Paid.\\par
2. Enter paid amount less than net total.\\par
3. Complete auth.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Due amount calculated correctly.\\par
2. Pending Payments entry is created.\\par
\\par
Test S05: Invalid paid amount\\par
1. Enter paid amount > net total.\\par
Expected: Validation blocks save.\\par
\\par
Test S06: Customer dedup by phone\\par
1. Create credit sale for phone `03XXXXXXXXX`.\\par
2. Create another credit sale with same phone and different name.\\par
Expected: Existing customer record is reused by phone.\\par
\\par
Test S07: Wrong pincode\\par
1. Enter wrong pincode in auth popup.\\par
Expected: Error message appears below pincode field.\\par
\\par
Test S08: Salesman attribution\\par
1. Save sales using different selected users in auth popup.\\par
Expected: Sales listing and receipts show correct salesperson attribution.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 7.5 Pending Payments Tests\\par
\\par
Test D01: Receive sale recovery\\par
1. Open open Sale due.\\par
2. Click Receive Payment.\\par
3. Submit partial amount.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Paid/Remaining update.\\par
2. Payment history records date, note, amount.\\par
3. Sale payment status updates.\\par
\\par
Test D02: Pay vendor payment\\par
1. Open open Purchase due.\\par
2. Click Pay Payment.\\par
3. Submit amount.\\par
Expected:\\par
1. Paid/Remaining update.\\par
2. Purchase table paid/remaining/status update.\\par
\\par
Test D03: Full settlement\\par
1. Pay/receive exact remaining amount.\\par
Expected: Status becomes Closed and action button is disabled.\\par
\\par
Test D04: Invoice link integrity\\par
1. Click invoice from sale due and purchase due rows.\\par
Expected: Correct detail page opens for affected record.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 7.6 Receipt and Invoice Print Tests\\par
\\par
Test R01: Sale invoice print data\\par
1. Open sale invoice detail and print.\\par
Expected printed output includes:\\par
1. Customer name\\par
2. Invoice number\\par
3. Sales person\\par
4. Items and amounts\\par
5. Gross, discount, net\\par
6. Paid amount\\par
7. Remaining amount\\par
8. Account status\\par
9. Payment status\\par
10. Sale type and method\\par
\\par
Test R02: Purchase invoice print data\\par
1. Open purchase invoice detail and print.\\par
Expected printed output includes:\\par
1. Vendor\\par
2. Salesman\\par
3. Invoice number\\par
4. Item table\\par
5. Total paid/remaining\\par
6. Account status and payment status\\par
7. Payment method when applicable\\par
\\par
Test R03: Number formatting\\par
1. Test with amounts above 1,000.\\par
Expected: Calculations and printed due/paid values stay correct.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
### 7.7 Customers, Returns, Stock, Analytics Tests\\par
\\par
Test C01: Customers summary\\par
1. Open Customers page.\\par
Expected: Sales amount/open due/last invoice are correct.\\par
\\par
Test RT01: Return processing\\par
1. Process return for valid invoice item.\\par
Expected: Return row appears and stock is increased.\\par
\\par
Test ST01: Stock valuation\\par
1. Open Stock page after multiple purchases/sales/returns.\\par
Expected: Quantities and valuation are consistent.\\par
\\par
Test AN01: Analytics widgets\\par
1. Open Analytics.\\par
Expected: Cards and charts render without JS/PHP errors.\\par
\\par
---\\par
\\par
